les sciences sociales et naturelles, de même que par la recherche comparative internationale. Il intéressera tant un large public que les professeurs, chercheurs, intervenants ou étudiants attentifs aux rapports complexes qu’entretiennent nos sociétés industrielles avancées avec l’environnement biophysique naturel et bâti.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEnvironmental managementxSocial aspects. 0aEnvironmental protectionxSocial aspects. 0aEnvironmental sciencesxSocial aspects. 0aEnvironmental sociology. 0aGreen movement. 0aHuman ecology. 0aSocial sciences. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Ecology.2bisacsh1 aAlian, Rajotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllard, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBartiaux, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChouinard, Omer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristelle, Gramaglia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClaeys-Mekdade, Cécilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeléage, Jean-Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlorence, Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFÂBUREL, Guillaume, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendron, Corinne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendron, Corinne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGirault, Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuilbeault, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKergreis, Sylive, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLescuyer, Gui